# Storyline

Follow the **storyline** skill. Read it from, in order of preference:

1. **This repo:** `.cursor/skills/storyline/SKILL.md` (if you copied the skill into the project), or  
2. **User skills:** `~/.cursor/skills/storyline/SKILL.md` (if installed with `npx skills add bjornno/skills --skill storyline`).

When the user **edits specs** and asks to **implement** or **align code**, locate the feature via **`specs/INDEX.md`** or **`OVERVIEW.md`** if needed, then read **`SPEC.md`** and linked files; treat acceptance as the target; then change code and update **Changelog**. If **`specs/ARCHITECTURE.md`** exists, read it when touching **cross-cutting** structure; update **`INDEX.md`** when feature spec paths change. Update **`ARCHITECTURE.md`** when you add or remove a repo-wide pattern that is not “standard Spring layering.”

Whenever you implement features, fix behavior-affecting bugs, or refactor user-visible behavior:

- Update the feature spec **the same session**: **`SPEC.md`** (monolith) **or** **`intent.md` / `experience.md` / `constraints.md`** when split—see the skill’s table. For APIs consumed by another app, add or refresh **`ui.md`**. Always append **`SPEC.md` Changelog**. Prioritize **why**, **flows**, **stories**, **acceptance**; keep **technical requirements** short. Do not mirror implementation. For **complex** flows, a **small Mermaid** diagram (user-facing labels) in `experience.md` or `SPEC.md`.
- Keep **`specs/OVERVIEW.md`** product-oriented; link to **`specs/<slug>/SPEC.md`** as the entry.
- New feature folders get a **Main capabilities** link in `OVERVIEW.md`.

Copy-paste phrases: `.cursor/skills/storyline/prompts.md` if present, else `~/.cursor/skills/storyline/prompts.md`. Slash commands: **`/storyline-*`** in `.cursor/commands/`.
